## Fix: Navbar role badge showed raw "ROLE" placeholder in local-dev

**Context**: Running locally the navbar role pill displayed the literal
placeholder text `ROLE` instead of `ADMIN`. Root cause: the `<li
id="roleNavBadgeItem">` in `base.html` carries Bootstrap's `.d-flex`
(`display:flex !important`), which beats the non-`!important`
`#roleNavBadgeItem { display:none }` base rule — so the pill is always laid out.
In local-dev mode `is_app_mode()` is false, so `applyRoleIndicators()`
early-returned and never called `showRoleNavBadge()`, leaving the server-rendered
`ROLE` placeholder visible. Local dev treats every caller as admin server-side,
so the pill should read `ADMIN`.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/js/permissions.js` — `applyRoleIndicators()` now
   renders the pill as `admin` when not in app mode (local dev), instead of
   returning early. App-mode behaviour (effective-role resolution + viewer
   lockdown) is unchanged.
2. `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css` — `#roleNavBadgeItem`
   base rule made `display: none !important` so it beats the `.d-flex` on the
   same element. This also prevents the `ROLE` placeholder from leaking for an
   app-mode caller whose effective role is empty (badge stays hidden until
   `.is-visible` is flipped).

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/static/global/js/permissions.js`
- `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css`

**Test result**: Front-end only (no Python touched). No new lint errors on the
edited files.

## Feature: Help Center full-page (maximize) toggle

**Context**: The in-app Help Center opens as an `modal-xl` dialog capped at
1100px wide / 88vh tall. Requested the ability to expand it to the whole page.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/templates/partials/layout/help_modal.html` — added a
   `#helpMaximizeToggle` button in the modal header (left of the close button)
   with a `bi-arrows-fullscreen` icon and `aria-pressed`.
2. `src/front/static/global/js/help-modal.js` — added `_applyMaximized()` /
   `_initMaximize()` (wired in `init()`). Clicking the button toggles a
   `help-modal-maximized` class on `#helpModal`, swaps the icon
   (fullscreen ↔ angle-contract) and the title/aria label, and persists the
   choice in `localStorage` (`ob.helpCenter.maximized`) so it reopens in the
   last-used size. Wrapped in try/catch for private-mode browsers.
3. `src/front/static/global/css/help-modal.css` — `.help-modal-maximized`
   makes the dialog full viewport (`width/height:100%`, `margin:0`,
   `modal-content` → `100vh`, square corners), with a 0.2s transition. Styled
   the header expand button to match the red header (translucent white).

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/templates/partials/layout/help_modal.html`
- `src/front/static/global/js/help-modal.js`
- `src/front/static/global/css/help-modal.css`

**Test result**: Front-end only (no Python touched). No new lint errors on the
edited files.
